servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

1 olive oil
3 potatoes
1 white turnip
1 carrot
1 Brown Onion
2 clove garlic
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese
1 tbs honey
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet mayonnaise
1 sachet Tunisian seasoning

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato and white turnip into bite-sized
chunks. Slice carrot into thick rounds. Slice
onion into wedges. Finely chop garlic.

• Place potato, turnip, carrot, onion and garlic
on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil,
sprinkle over Tunisian seasoning, then season
with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between
two trays.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over
medium-high heat.
• Toast flaked almonds, tossing occasionally,
until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Pat haloumi dry with paper towel, then cut into
1cm slices.
• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook haloumi, turning,
until golden brown all over, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the honey to the pan and turn haloumi to
coat, 1 minute.

• When the veggies are done, transfer them to a
large bowl and allow to cool slightly.
• Once cooled slightly, add spinach & rocket mix
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Season to
taste and toss to combine.

• Divide spiced veggie toss between plates. Top
with honey-glazed haloumi.
• Garnish with toasted almonds. Serve with
mayonnaise. Enjoy!